  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "SimTown is a 1995 video game published by Maxis, much like the best selling SimCity but on a smaller scale. SimTown allows the player to construct a town consisting of streets, houses, businesses and parks and then control the people in it. SimTown was one of the many 'Sim' spin-offs at the time, and was targeted more towards children.\n\nThe Super Famicom/Super Nintendo Entertainment System version of SimTown is called SimCity Jr. (シムシティJr.). It was published by Imagineer.",
